The Quick(ish) start guide. Destined to make you fame and fortune unless
you die.

Firstly pick the Ross 154 starting position.

This will put you in a position where the most hostile enemy is yourself.

Press F4
Pick the stockyard.
Click on the down arrow until you see Hydrogen fuel, buy as much as possible.

Press F4 again.
Go to the Bulitin Board.
Go right to the bottom, and click on the message
	`SHIP REQUIRED. Payment of c520 (c=credits) for a ship
         to take a small package to the Fomalhaut system'
Click on the small box next to it.
You can if you like ask for more money or a permit but it is not needed
Click on `OK - Agreed'
Then Hang up.

Next go up to the FEDERAL MILITARY message.
Click on the little box next to it.
Well, as your going to the Fomalhult system any way, why not kill two birds
with one stone and accept the delivery misson they are offering.
As you will see they have a strict policy and dont fuck about.
Accept the misson.
Hang up.

[N.B. always hang up as sometimes the Bulitin boards crash.]

Press F4 again.
Pick Launch Request option.
Launch by pressing F7
Point the nose of the ship in the air and hit the thruster (return)

		RETURN is set thrust faster
		R.SHIFT is set thrust slower/backwords

Thrust until you reach 12000 Meters. This is the Altitude in which
Hyperspace is permitted.

Press F2.
Move the cursor keys around until you find the Lacaille (Down and right)
system. When you have a hyperspace lock the system will have a green halo
about it.

Press F1 to get to the forward view.
Now on the 8th icon along you have a hyper space option. DO IT!

You will find your self (unless you have a mis-jump, but thats unlikely
in a recently serviced ship like yours) now in the Lacaille system. This
place is a dump lets get out of here.

Press F2
Move up and left with the cursor keys (if you find you have rotated this
map then the button c sets it back to normallity) to the Fomahult system.

FRONT VIEW. HYPERSPACE.

You are now in the fomahult system. The place you can make some serious
money from.

Oaky, press F2 twice and you will have a green screen displaying the
current system, yes I could go in to detail about how to use this and
what different things do but we here just dont have the time.

Now if you have explored your icons already you will know that there are
only a few places in this system you can dock at. To make it easy we
will pick a space station.

There are loads of places all off the Gas giant Fomahult 4, but those
are difficult to get to sometimes due to your hyperspace entrance to the
system in relation to the gravitational pull of different planets.

So instead we will pick a nice vacation ground called Conversion.
On this menu F7 and F8 zoom in and out respectivley.
By holding down the right mouse button and moving the mouse the system
moves also. Rotate it until you see Conversion and zoom in.

Now this Could take bloody ages so it is time to use the function turbo
zoom. by double clicking on this icon you are hurled to as close as 
possible to your selected target.

If you havent clicked on Conversion then you will be looking at the star
of the system. Hold down on zoom out F8 and you will see some light green
orbital lines come in to view and on the third one out will be Conversion.
Click on it and it will Auto center. Double click zoom in and then zoom out
from conversion to find the orbiting station, Dobson Terminal.

Now F10 is the autopilot locking system, so get the space station into view
(it doesnt matter how close as long as you can see the words) and click f10
then on a space just before the D of Dobson. This will give you a lock.

Phew. Okay now you have a lock get back to the front view.
F7 is the autopliot/manual/engines off icon so click it around until you
get the autopilot on.

Now the autopilot is engaged and as the game runs in real time it takes
literaly days to travel accros even small areas of space. To aid us in
our quest a stardreamer option is available.

Basically the stardreamer controls speed up time. Above the first few icons
is a small console. This is the stardreamer control. From left to right the
options are:

 Stop/pause: this also gives you a options screen which is easy to work
	     out. It has options to turn off stars and detail control, all
	     of these speed up the game when down to their lowest setting.
 
Play		Obvious realy.
Play x 10	
Play x 100	
Play x 1000	
Play x 10000	

So Play is normal time. Not if you want to hang around for years I seriously
suggest pressing the fastest time option, of course you do get attacked alot,
but that is a by product, as you are beginner then I doubt iff you will
have hundreds of ships on your ass.

So, your in the Fomalhult system, on autopilot, heading to Dobson Terminal
on maximum time x 10000 mode. The distancing will be displayed in AU
(Astronmical UNITS) and Kilometers.

When you get really close your ship will automatically ask for docking 
permission. Unless your a lover of art then speed up the time to max to
dock quickly.

Enter the Bulitin Board and wait a bit, after a while you will recive a 
promotion form the FEDERATION and some cash from the bimbo.

Now you have cash you can retire!

Well not really just over 800 credits is enough to let you retire after
trading.

HOW TO MAKE LOADS BY TRADING.

Okay you are the proud owner of an Eagle long range fighter, which is
just a flashy name for shitty. You really do have very little cargo space
in the Eagle so it is Important to get as much profit as possible into
your flying feces.

From where you are the easiest profit to get is to trade robots on a
Fomalhult to CD 37 (just right of Fomahult). You can now buy 1 tonne of
robots and trade back with Fomahult.

To make extra money, buy the time you have reached Fomahult before selling
the robots on the stockmarket try the Bulitin Board. Quite often you can 
find some loony willing to buy robots off you for around 2000 credits.

Doing this often gets you cash quick and sharpish!

